    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix header type initialization in OTG packet generator\n\n### Summary\nThe OTG traffic generator contained an uninitialized variable bug in the `header_size_gen` function that could cause incorrect header type values to be set. The issue occurred when computing packet header types based on IP version and transport protocol combinations.\n\nThe bug manifested as incorrect protocol identification in generated traffic packets, particularly under scenarios with mixed IPv4/IPv6 and TCP/UDP traffic patterns. Packets would occasionally be marked with wrong header types, causing parsing errors in downstream processing.\n\nThe root cause was the use of `+=` operations on the `header_type_app` field without proper initialization, leading to accumulation of incorrect values when the function was invoked multiple times.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OTG/otg_tx.c`: Fixed header type initialization and assignment in `header_size_gen` function\n- Properly initialize `header_type_app` to `NO_HEADER` before setting values\n- Replace accumulation operations with direct assignments for correct header type mapping\n- Ensure IPv4/IPv6 and TCP/UDP combinations map to correct enum values\n\n"
}